-- Spain May Cut Renewable Power Subsidies Today, Cinco Dias Says
-- B y   B e n   S i l l s
-- 2012-08-03T05:28:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-03/spain-may-cut-renewable-power-subsidies-today-cinco-dias-says.html
Spain  may cut subsidies for renewable
energy plants at the weekly cabinet meeting in  Madrid  today,
Cinco Dias said, citing industry rumors.  Energy and Industry Minister Jose Manuel Soria said this
week he may reduce aid after his plan to impose taxes on the
generators failed to win the support of the rest of the
government, the newspaper said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
